org.javassonne.model
Class TileSet

java.lang.Object
  org.javassonne.model.TileSet

public class TileSet
extends java.lang.Object

The tile set class represents a collection of tiles, and stores the number of times each one may be drawn during the game. Tile sets may be loaded from disk using the TileSerializer class, and should be created using the TileSetCreator. Tile sets are different from tile decks. A tile set represents a single collection of tiles - for example, the tiles from an expansion pack. A tile deck may contain multiple tile sets, and represents the pool of tiles the user is actually playing with. Additionally, a tile set contains a single copy of each tile object, while the tile deck may contain multiple.

bengotow
